Apple’s common‑stock outstanding fell from 16,426,786 thousand shares at the start of 2022 to 15,116,786 thousand shares at the end of 2024 – a total decline of 1,310,000 thousand shares (≈ 1.31 billion shares)【AAPL_10k_2024.pdf page 45】. Each year the decrease equals the net effect of repurchases versus issuances:  

* 2022: repurchased 568,589 k, issued 85,228 k → net‑repurchase ‑483,361 k;  
* 2023: repurchased 471,419 k, issued 78,055 k → net‑repurchase ‑393,364 k;  
* 2024: repurchased 499,372 k, issued 66,097 k → net‑repurchase ‑433,275 k【AAPL_10k_2024.pdf page 46】.  

Summing these net repurchases (‑483,361 k ‑ 393,364 k ‑ 433,275 k = ‑1,310,000 k) shows that the 1.31‑billion‑share reduction is driven entirely by share repurchases exceeding issuances over the 2022‑2024 period.
